## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Three REPL interaction features matching Claude Code / Codex CLI conventions:

1. **Command history** — up/down arrows cycle through previously submitted commands. Current input is preserved when browsing and restored when pressing down past the end.

2. **Escape to cancel** — escape from any overlay view (progress, tree, gate, diff) returns to the REPL input with a "Cancelled." message. Activity indicator is cleared.

3. **Activity indicator** — spinner + text line rendered above the prompt when the engine is active. SetActivity("text") shows it, SetActivity("") clears it. Ready for engine execution wiring. Creative word prompt (word of the day etc.) to be designed later.

